{
  "texts": [
    "The 775 nm pump beam is focused by a lens (f = 150 mm, not shown) at the PPLN2 with a radius of 70 μm to enhance SPDC efficiency.",
    "To filter out the 775 nm pump beam, two 1550 nm bandpass filters, each with a 10 nm bandwidth, are utilized.",
    "Both crystals satisfy type-0 phase matching condition and are mounted on the temperaturecontrolled stages to uphold the optimal phase matching temperature: 56.6 °C for PPLN1 and 82 °C for PPLN2.",
    "Accounting for system losses, detector efficiency, and a heralding efficiency of approximately 14.5%, the characterized source brightness stands at ~3:79 10 6 pairs/s/ nm/mW.",
    "Photon pairs generated via SPDC are separated by a BS, and then one of them is coupled into free-space by a collimator (Thorlabs F260FC-1550) at a beam waist of 1.5 mm."
  ]
}